This paper deals with image style transfer, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of different loss functions and computational efficiency, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of depth-wise separable convolution and nearest neighbor interpolation are techniques commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
